/- A space is a "normed space" if it has a norm function from the underlying
  field to an ordered field, such that the norm of a scalar multiple of a vector
  is the scalar's norm times the vector's norm. -/
def IsNormedSpace (𝕜 : Type u_1) [NormedField 𝕜] [AddCommGroupWithOne 𝕜] [OrderedAddCommMonoid 𝕜] [Nontrivial 𝕜] [OrderedAddCommMonoid' 𝕜] [LinearOrderedAddCommMonoid' 𝕜] [DivisionRing 𝕜] [OrderedDivisionRing 𝕜] (E : Type u_3) [AddCommGroup E] [NormedAddGroup E] [OrderedAddCommMonoid E] [OrderedAddCommMonoid' E] [LinearOrderedAddCommMonoid' E] (N : 𝕜 → E → ℝ≥0∞) : Prop :=
